==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Up-to-date
<hw>Up`-to-date"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Extending to the
present time; having style, manners, knowledge, or other qualities that
are abreast of the times.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A general <xex>up-to-date</xex>
style of presentment.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Nature.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Everything's
up-to-date in Kansas City.⟦rdquo⟧</p>

<p><q>I must prefer to translate the poet in a manner more congenial if
less <qex>up-to-date</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Andrew Lang.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>up-to-the-minute</ent>⟦br⟧
